p: The high efficacy of compound 5f in cell arrest at G2/M phase and in cell apoptosis as indicated by its results in Table 3 relative to its congeners 5d and 5e aligns with its potent effect on MCF-7 as indicated by its IC 50 (2.27 μM) in comparison to the IC 50 of compounds 5d and 5e (3.41 and 3.45 μM, respectively).
